[2]
Date: Wed 25 Jun 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Go Asia Pacific, via ABC Radio Australia News, Wed 25 Jun 2003 [edited]
<http://www.goasiapacific.com/news/GoAsiaPacificBNA_888285.htm>

Chinese Provinces Act Against Japanese Encephalitis
---------------------------------------------------
An outbreak of mosquito-borne Japanese encephalitis, which has killed at
least 19 people, has spread to 2 more Chinese provinces. State media says
at least 18 children have died among 211 infected by the disease in
southern Guangdong, and cases have now been reported in central Hunan
province and China's southernmost province of Hainan. The China News
Service says while numbers are down on last year, residents are being urged
to take measures to prevent infections.
--
